metadata.title: Once my card order is placed, how can I track my order?
metadata.doc: You will be able to track your FamCard on the card screen. Just click on "Track order" and you can watch your FamCard until it reaches your doorstep.

metadata.title: I am a parent. Can I order the FamCard for my teen?
metadata.doc: Yes, you can order the FamCard for your kid but not through your app. We would need your teen to be onboard with us. Invite your teen on the app, help them in setting up the profile and completing their KYC and that's it. You can order the FamCard for your teen from their account.

metadata.title: How can I order the FamCard?
metadata.doc:
You can order the card in 4 simple steps:

- Click on "Order Card" on the card screen
- Personalise your card with your details
- Fill in your delivery address
- Pay for the card and place your order

metadata.title: Who can order the FamCard?
metadata.doc:
FamCard is available to teenagers who are 20 and below.

For teens below the age of 18:
- They must have completed their own KYC
- They must have their parent's permission (consent) to use FamPay

metadata.title: How can I become a Friend of Fam?
metadata.doc: There are no specific eligibility criteria except that you need to be passionate. Our selection process consists of a couple of interviews and the most driven kids are hand-picked into the community.

metadata.title: What benefits are enjoyed by Friends of Fam?
metadata.doc:
- Certificate and recommendations
- Exclusive FamPay swag kit
- Featured on FamPay Instagram
- Sponsored social outings

metadata.title: What activities are organised for Friends of Fam?
metadata.doc: FamPay aims to achieve the role of catalyst in furthering the motives for which Friends of Fam stand for through various online and offline events, volunteering opportunities and mentoring.

metadata.title: Who are Friends of Fam?
metadata.doc: Friends of Fam is a community of driven teenagers who channelize their hunger for growth into tangible endeavors early on in life.

metadata.title: Who is the owner of the family?
metadata.doc: Only adults can be the owner of the family. So the adult that gets invited to the family and completes at least the minimum KYC verification first before all the other invited adults, becomes the owner.

metadata.title: What is my family profile?
metadata.doc: Your family profile includes a custom family name, display and list of all the members.

metadata.title: I am a minor. How should I add money to my FamPay account?
metadata.doc: As a minor, you cannot add money to your FamPay account. However, you can nudge/request a friend or request from your Parents/Guardian on FamPay to load your prepaid account. Growing up will come soon to you.

metadata.title: How do I get started on FamPay?
metadata.doc:
Quite simple actually!

1. Download the app and setup your account with the necessary KYC verification. 
2. Order your FamCard
3. Request money from parents
4. Start saving / shopping on the app (you can use FamCard or Scan and pay)
5. You can also send money to friends and help a friend in need.

metadata.title: Why do I need FamPay?
metadata.doc:
Do the following scenarios look relatable to you? 
- I have to carry enough cash with me all the time, in case I have to get something on the way back home
- My parents run out of cash to give to me when I need to go out. 
- I have to keep borrowing money from friends when I fall short of cash
- I have to often ask my parents for their OTP whenever I use the card
- I am dependent on my parents for online/offline payments. 

There can be many more such scenarios. If these look relatable, then FamPay can help you. 

With FamPay, you get your own FamCard. You can get your parents to load your FamPay prepaid account anytime online, and you can pay online/offline, anytime, anywhere.

metadata.title: Is it safe? How?
metadata.doc:
Yes, FamPay is secure. 
We don't blame you for thinking twice security, especially when it comes to trusting someone, or something with your money. Allow us to explain how FamPay is safe and secure for teens and families!

- We have 100% end to end secured systems
- We are partnered with IDFC First Bank (issuer bank)
- The accounts on FamPay are not linked to any bank account
- We offer maximum transparency and there are absolutely no hidden charges
- The FamCard has no numbers printed on the physical card, instead it is stored on the app, which makes it very secure.
- There’s no fear of card information getting misused in case it gets stolen or lost and the card can be paused, blocked and managed at your fingertips on the app.
- All transactions are device-lock protected
- Parents can choose to monitor your child's transactions
- Teens cannot add money by themselves, they can only request for money.

Its really simple to start using FamPay. 
- Download the app, and setup your account with the necessary KYC verification. 
- Invite your child and get them to complete their KYC verification too. 
- Load their FamPay prepaid account online instead of giving cash/your cards/OTPs and get them to spend, save and learn!

metadata.title: Why do I need FamPay?
metadata.doc:
Have you ever had to - 

- search for the OTP in the middle of a meeting to give to your teen who is shopping online/ offline?
- run to the ATM when you ran out of cash to give to your teen for their school project/book fees? 
- worry about giving your debit/credit card to your teen when they were going on a class trip? 

If yes, FamPay can help solve all your problems. 
With FamPay, your teen gets their own FamCard (numberless prepaid card). You can load their account anytime online, and they can shop online/offline, anytime, anywhere, under your supervision. You can track their expenses as well.

metadata.title: What is FamPay's mission?
metadata.doc:
Over 300 million adults (age 18+) in India pay digitally, but 250 million minors (age 11-18) can not, despite having smartphones, internet and being tech savvy. Minors are still forced to use cash or use their parents debit/credit cards for payments. Over 80% of teens love shopping online but 67% of them are forced to use cash and 52% use parents cards/ payment apps.

FamPay is solving this problem by helping teens make payments online/offline independently under their parents supervision, without the need of a bank account. As part of our mission, we are raising a new, financially aware generation of Indians who understand the fundamentals of personal finance and are capable of making decisions in their best long term interest.

metadata.title: Who is it for?
metadata.doc:
FamPay is specially designed for teens and their families. Anyone of age 11 or above is eligible to setup a FamPay account. 
Teens (age 11-20) and Parents of Teens (age 35+) can create a FamPay account without an invite. If you are between 21 to 34 years of age, you need to have an invite to create a FamPay account.

metadata.title: What is FamPay?
metadata.doc:
FamPay offers prepaid card payments for teenagers.
Up until now, only adults (age 18+) could make digital payments using online/mobile banking or payments apps. With FamPay and its numberless prepaid card, minors (below 18) can successfully make online and offline payments without the need to set up a bank account.

metadata.title: How do I use the card at offline stores?
metadata.doc: To use the card at offline stores, you need to order a physical card for yourself which can be used to swipe or tap for payments. Also, it's quite cool to carry. ;)

metadata.title: Where can I use FamCard?
metadata.doc:
You can swipe your FamCard or use the Tap N Pay feature in person or transfer money digitally on all your favourite sites, such as Amazon, Netflix, Zomato, Swiggy,  etc.
Book your movie tickets, get a cab, buy a gift, grab a snack! Wherever there's a fun-way, there's FamPay!

metadata.title: What makes FamCard so special?
metadata.doc:
Lots of things, but here goes a few!

Personalized and Trendy: Teens can get their favourite doodles and names personalized on the FamCard in a signature-like style. So, if you wanna be named Batman, then you can get it printed on your card!

Numberless and Secure: FamCard has no numbers printed on the physical card which makes it very secure. The card number and other details (expiry date, CVV) are stored securely within the FamPay app instead of being printed on the physical card. There’s no fear of card information getting disclosed in case it gets stolen or lost and the card can be paused, blocked and managed at fingertips on the app. Additionally, the card details within the app can be accessed only with device lock like fingerprint, face ID, pattern lock or PIN.

Contactless and Safe: It also has the feature of Tap N Pay, through which teens can transact at offline merchants (upto INR.2000) by tapping their card against the POS (Point of Sale) machines.

metadata.title: What is a FamCard?
metadata.doc:
FamCard is a numberless prepaid card cobranded and issued by IDFC FIRST bank. 

As soon as you create an account with us, you'll be able to access your card in the app for all your online purchases. To swipe the card at offline merchants, you need to place an order for the physical card.
